# Energy-flow dashboard — restart server after changes

When you **create or edit** files that affect the local dashboard at `http://127.0.0.1:8765/`, **stop and restart the server yourself** before telling the user to test. Do not ask the user to restart manually.

## When to restart

**Always restart** after changes to:

- `energy_flow/server.py`
- Any other `energy_flow/*.py` (e.g. `modbus_client.py`, `history_loader.py`, `live_buffer.py`)
- `luxpower_fetch_month.py` or other modules imported by the server

**Static-only changes** (`energy_flow/static/**` — HTML, JS, CSS): server restart not required; remind user to **Ctrl+F5** hard refresh. Still restart if you also changed Python in the same task.

## How to restart (Windows — run yourself)

```powershell
$p = (Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 8765 -State Listen -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -First 1).OwningProcess
if ($p) { Stop-Process -Id $p -Force }
Start-Sleep -Seconds 1
cd "C:\Users\User\Ai Projects\Business Ideas\energy_flow"
Start-Process python -ArgumentList "server.py" -WindowStyle Hidden
```

Verify it is listening:

```powershell
curl.exe -s -o NUL -w "%{http_code}" http://127.0.0.1:8765/api/history/sync
```

Expect `200`.

## Report back

After restarting, tell the user:

- That the server was restarted on port **8765**
- For static/JS changes, to **Ctrl+F5** the browser
- If sync/API behaviour changed, to try **Sync cloud data** again
